## Title
OpenClaw Identity

## Recommendation Summary

### Intent Assessment
Defines the persistent Claude identity framework via soul.md (values), being.md (memory), and heartbeat.md (health), enabling AI agent continuity across sessions.

### Categorization Changes
- **ZETT**: "none (status: qualifying)" → "content_stage: evergreen" (Original conceptual framework for AI identity persistence. Novel thinking — evergreen. Missing content_stage field.)
- **TREE**: "technology/ai-ml, meta/pkm" → "meta/beestgraph/architecture, technology/ai-ml/agents" (This is about beestgraph architecture. technology/ai-ml/agents is more specific than technology/ai-ml.)
- **GRAPH**: "Likely has Document node" → "Ensure edges to Heartbeat System, Qualification Pipeline, The Herd Protocol. AI Agent Identity, Session Continuity, Persistent Personality should be Concept nodes." (Identity framework connects to multiple system components.)

### Metadata Issues
Missing content_stage field. Status qualifying — should be published as a core architectural doc. Missing created_at/updated_at. Summary is well-written. Tags are appropriate.

