### Enrichment
AI agent memory is a rapidly evolving field in 2026. Mem0 (state of AI agent memory 2026), Letta (persistent identity with editable memory blocks), and AWS AgentCore all tackle session persistence. Key insight from research: memory persistence across sessions creates new security risks (Echoleak incident 2024). Structured memory attributes (added Jun 2025) enable queryable metadata alongside semantic content. The OpenClaw three-file approach (soul/being/heartbeat) is simpler and more transparent than framework-based solutions.

